                                    <cell>B</cell>
                                    <cell>A</cell>
                                    <cell>A</cell>
                                </row>
                            </tabular>
                        </table>
                    </p>
                    
                    <me>A = 80 \cdot 2 + 120 \cdot 1 = 280</me>
                    <me>B = 80 \cdot 1 + 120 \cdot 2 = 320</me>
                    
                    <p>B wins</p>
                    
                    <p>Since the winner changed when a losing candidate (C), dropped out of the 
                        race, the IIA (Independence of Irrelevant Alternatives) criterion 
                        was violated.</p>
                </solution>
                
                <answer>B wins. Since the winner changed when a losing candidate (C), dropped out 
                    of the 
                        race, the IIA (Independence of Irrelevant Alternatives) criterion 
                        was violated.</answer>
                                        
